Stock Fraud News & Information

Published By Fitapelli | Kurta





           Stock Fraud News & Information         STOCK FRAUD CLAIMS PRODUCTS PRESS     












Published on: May 14, 2015
Cape Securities, Inc. fined $125,000 for failure to supervise

By Fitapelli Kurta






 


Broker-dealer firm, Cape Securities, Inc. was fined $125,000 by the Financial Industry Regulatory Authority (FINRA) on May 5, 2015 for failing to supervise and prevent unsuitable investment recommendations and churning of customer accounts.
According to the Letter of Acceptance, Waiver and Consent (AWC) from October 2011 through February 2013, Cape Securities, Inc.’s Manhattan branch sold numerous unsuitable leveraged ETFs (Exchange Traded Funds) to customers, resulting in excessive commissions for Cape Securities, Inc. Cape Securities, Inc. failed to warn investors of the inherent risks associated with leveraged ETF’s, however and failed to contact the customer’s about the trading in their accounts.
Cape Securities, Inc. also failed to detect several fraudulent wire transfers. In two cases the customer’s alleged to have requested the transactions had died before the date of the request.

Georgia based Cape Securities broker, Michael A. Lovett was fined $5,000 and suspended from the securities industry for six months for failing to supervise brokers.
New York based Cape Securities broker, Robert J. Rowan III pled guilty to criminal sale of a controlled substance and possession of a controlled substance, in February 2011.

If you have lost money investing with Cape Securities, Inc. you may be entitled to full recovery of your losses. The attorneys at Fitapelli Kurta prosecute cases on behalf of investors like you who have lost money as a result of unsuitable investments. These cases are taken on a contingency fee basis only, which means our firm will not receive any compensation whatsoever unless and until you recover money.
Cases are filed with the Financial Industry Regulatory Authority (FINRA) and will submit to arbitration. Fitapelli Kurta has filed hundreds of cases before FINRA and has recovered millions on behalf of investors who have fallen victim to broker misconduct. Call 877 – 238 – 4175 to speak directly to an attorney and further discuss the merits of your case.
Our consultations are always free. Time is of the essence so do not delay.
Call 877 – 238 – 4175 now














Contact Us
FREE CASE EVALUATION TOLL FREE: 877.238.4175 LOCAL PHONE: 212.658.1500


















